<p>John Bolton, who served as national security adviser during President Trump’s first term, was indicted on Thursday by a federal grand jury on 18 counts related to retaining and transmitting classified national defense information [france24.com#1][aljazeera.com#2][theglobeandmail.com#1][bbc.com#1]. Prosecutors allege he stored top secret records at home and shared diary-like notes containing sensitive details with two relatives for possible use in a book [theglobeandmail.com#1][scmp.com#1]. The case is the third in recent weeks involving a prominent critic of the President, a pattern that has prompted concerns about political targeting from some observers [dw.com#1][euronews.com#1][bbc.com#1]. Bolton denies wrongdoing and has criticized the charges [timesofisrael.com#1][abc.net.au#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/38Z3c8lVxl07TrHdgP21_18PFDyAikXlfZEBJMvMRAu1jpkyuycFu8P66xvb2-VbgdiE5w45-RXkFe1OJijOc8YhI9EBDSOvKYiq1EWXXvrWcGe4cikWWu25QVMhwN-IEyr5NnLhxX01MVHNuTVewftAE-nlhRbk6hVZeaKjk1TSUfTKEfJL0MiHphjpHp5vCVN-NxuclX20i6zA-TYsjyldfqtln6EVoNt_huudAxca4aGXA2vEmMoeKLyOe-Dg8MpooBsw4mWk-dyqxA' alt='John Bolton pictured in Washington; prosecutors allege he mishandled classified records.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Charge breakdown: The indictment includes eight counts for transmitting national defense information and ten counts for unlawful retention [ndtv.com#1].</li><li>Diary notes: Prosecutors say Bolton shared diary-like notes about his government service with relatives, which the indictment alleges contained classified material [theglobeandmail.com#1].</li><li>Maryland venue: The case was unsealed in Maryland, where a federal grand jury returned the indictment [firstpost.com#1].</li><li>Espionage Act basis: Charges center on the alleged transmission and retention of national defense information under the Espionage Act [dw.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Email breach claim: The indictment references a 2021 notification that Bolton’s email had been hacked, with investigators attributing the intrusion to an Iran-linked actor [theglobeandmail.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>John Bolton: He denies mishandling sensitive information and called the indictment an &quot;abuse of power.&quot;. (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/john-bolton-charged-with-sharing-classified-info-in-emails-hacked-by-iran-linked-actor/'>The Times of Israel</a>)</li><li>US Department of Justice: The government alleges Bolton unlawfully retained and transmitted classified national defense information. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20251016-john-bolton-indicted-us-defence-secrets'>France 24</a>)</li><li>President Trump: He publicly disparaged Bolton following the indictment, calling him a &quot;bad guy.&quot;. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2025/oct/17/donald-trump-john-bolton-volodymyr-zelenskyy-us-politics-latest-news-updates'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Critics and analysts: Some expressed concern that the Justice Department is targeting political opponents while allies face less scrutiny. (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/17/trump-critic-and-ex-national-security-adviser-john-bolton-criminally-indicted'>Euronews</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/united-states-canada/article/3329309/ex-trump-aide-john-bolton-charged-amid-crackdown-us-presidents-critics'>Ex-Trump aide John Bolton charged amid crackdown on US president’s critics</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/john-bolton-former-trump-national-security-adviser-indicted/a-74392911'>John Bolton: Former Trump national security adviser indicted</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-john-bolton-trump-indict-charge-classified-information/'>John Bolton, Trump’s former national security adviser, indicted for mishandling classified information</a> - theglobeandmail.com</li><li><a href='https://www.csmonitor.com/USA/P